    "content_hash": "ddb9123b81f6ccb3",
    "department": "Recruiting",
    "description": "WHY HARVEY\n\nAt Harvey, we’re transforming how legal and professional services operate — not incrementally, but end-to-end. By combining frontier agentic AI, an enterprise-grade platform, and deep domain expertise, we’re reshaping how critical knowledge work gets done for decades to come.\n\nThis is a rare chance to help build a generational company at a true inflection point. With 1000+ customers in 60+ countries, strong product-market fit, and world-class investor support, we’re scaling fast and defining a new category in real time. The work is ambitious, the bar is high, and the opportunity for growth — personal, professional, and financial — is unmatched.\n\nOur team is sharp, motivated, and deeply committed to the mission. We move fast, operate with intensity, and take real ownership of the problems we tackle — from early thinking to long-term outcomes. We stay close to our customers — from leadership to engineers — and work together to solve real problems with urgency and care. If you thrive in ambiguity, push for excellence, and want to help shape the future of work alongside others who raise the bar, we invite you to build with us.\n\nAt Harvey, the future of professional services is being written today — and we’re just getting started.\n\n\nROLE OVERVIEW\n\nWe’re looking for a full-time Executive Recruiting Coordinator to join our Talent team at Harvey AI and play a critical role in delivering a best-in-class hiring experience, particularly for senior and executive-level candidates.\n\nIn this role, you’ll operate as a strategic partner to Executive recruiters, Executive Assistants (EAs), and leadership — ensuring that every interaction reflects Harvey’s high standards and attention to detail. You’ll own complex scheduling across senior stakeholders, manage high-touch candidate logistics, and lead onsite execution with a “white glove” approach.\n\nHarvey is growing rapidly, with a significant focus on building out our leadership team. This means navigating intricate calendars, coordinating across multiple time zones, and supporting broader coordination efforts alongside EAs and business partners. You’ll be at the center of this process — bringing polish, discretion, and operational excellence to every step.\n\nThis is a hybrid role based in our San Francisco office. You’ll be expected to be onsite for in-person interviews and executive visits, ensuring a thoughtful, elevated experience for both candidates and interviewers.\n\nAt Harvey, we’re building cutting-edge AI products that are transforming the way professionals work. You’ll join a fast-paced, high-performing, and deeply collaborative team that values precision, care, and excellence. If you thrive in dynamic environments, enjoy working closely with senior stakeholders, and take pride in delivering exceptional experiences, we’d love to meet you.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Partner closely with recruiters, hiring managers, senior leadership, and Executive Assistants to deliver a seamless, high-touch candidate experience — with a focus on executive hiring\n\n - Own end-to-end scheduling for executive and senior candidates, managing complex calendars across multiple stakeholders and time zones\n\n - Act as a primary point of contact for candidates, providing proactive communication, white glove support, and a highly personalized experience throughout the process\n\n - Contribute to broader business coordination efforts as a member of the coordination team\n\n - Anticipate scheduling conflicts and proactively resolve issues, balancing competing priorities with speed and discretion\n\n - Ensure in-person interview days and executive visits are flawlessly executed, handling logistics end-to-end and troubleshooting in real time\n\n - Maintain and optimize scheduling workflows and systems (Ashby), ensuring data accuracy and operational excellence\n\n - Partner with the Recruiting Operations teams on initiatives to improve processes, scale recruiting coordination, and elevate the candidate experience\n\n\nWHAT YOU HAVE\n\n - 5+ years of experience in recruiting coordination, executive scheduling, EA support, or operations in a fast-paced environment\n\n - Experience supporting senior stakeholders or executives, with an understanding of discretion and stakeholder management\n\n - Proven ability to manage complex scheduling and onsite coordination across multiple stakeholders and time zones\n\n - Strong experience in candidate-facing work, with a focus on delivering high-touch, concierge-level experiences\n\n - Experience partnering with Executive Assistants or supporting cross-functional coordination efforts\n\n - Experience with Ashby or a similar applicant tracking system\n\n - Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail, with the ability to anticipate needs and stay ahead of shifting priorities\n\n - Strong communication skills — polished, clear, and professional across all channels\n\n - A calm, solutions-oriented mindset with the ability to adapt quickly and operate under pressure\n\n - A service-oriented approach and a genuine passion for delivering a best-in-class candidate experience\n\n - Proficiency in Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Calendar, etc.)\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\n$96,000-144,000 USD\n\n\nDEPENDING ON YOUR LOCATION, AN APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICE MAY APPLY TO YOU. YOU CAN FIND ALL OF OUR APPLICANT PRIVACY NOTICES [HERE https://www.notion.so/harveyai/Harvey-Candidate-Privacy-Policies-319ac3fcdd7a803bb807d5094f249922].\n\n\n\n\nHarvey is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity/expression, national origin, disability, age, genetic information, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy or related condition, or any other basis protected by law.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made by emailing accommodations@harvey.ai",
